  FAMOUS PEOPLE
============================================================

Name:          Isaac Newton
Lived:         1643 - 1727
Nationality:   English
Field:         Physics/Math
Known For:     Laws of Motion, Gravity
Contribution:  Principia Mathematica; invented calculus; explained planetary motion
Quote:         "If I have seen further, it is by standing on the shoulders of giants."

Name:          Florence Nightingale
Lived:         1820 - 1910
Nationality:   English
Field:         Medicine
Known For:     Modern nursing
Contribution:  Founded modern nursing; used statistics; reduced Crimean War mortality 40% to 2%
Quote:         "I attribute my success to this: I never gave or took any excuse."

Name:          Aristotle
Lived:         384 - -322
Nationality:   Greek
Field:         Philosophy
Known For:     Logic, ethics, biology
Contribution:  Codified logic; wrote on biology, physics, ethics, politics; tutored Alexander
Quote:         "The more you know, the more you know you don't know."

============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Godel's Incompleteness
Branch:       Logic
Formula:      Every consistent system has unprovable true statements
Applications: AI limits, foundations of math
Discoverer:   Kurt Godel (1931)

Theorem/Law:  Nash Equilibrium
Branch:       Game Theory
Formula:      No player benefits from unilateral strategy change
Applications: Economics, AI, political science
Discoverer:   John Nash (1950)

Theorem/Law:  Four Color Theorem
Branch:       Topology
Formula:      Any planar map needs at most 4 colors
Applications: Cartography, graph coloring
Discoverer:   Appel and Haken (1976)

